credit_line: Gift of Mabel Nast Crawford and Cyril Nast
title: British Free Trade Scare
medium: pen and ink on illustration board
inscriptions: l.r. in ink: Th:Nast./ 1888.; u.l.: [embossed stamp]; verso c. in ink: A Substitute fro the Senate to get more votes!/ A big step in the direction toward pricing (?) up free trade queues,/ Showing unusual favoritism to the rich and throwing more stones/ to the poor, instead of the necessities of life./ The End of this Queue Farce.
